<center>
<img src="line.gif"><br>
<img src="drjlogo.gif"><br>
<img src="line.gif"><br>
</center>

<center><font size="6">
THE
EIGHTH<br> 
INTERNATIONAL<br> 
DISASTER 
RECOVERY <br>
SYMPOSIUM 
AND
EXHIBITION<br></font size>
<br>
<font size="4">
September 9 - 11, 1996<br>
Atlanta, GA<br>
Disaster Recovery Journal presents its 15th conference<br></center></font size>
<br>
<br><hr><center><font size="5">
A Welcome from Richard Arnold<br></center></font size>
<hr><br>
<IMG SRC="speakers/rich.gif" img align=left>
Dear Disaster Recovery Planner,<br>
<br>
This summer, Atlanta will be a busy place as the Olympic Games debut in that city. These games will be attended by hundreds of athletes who have devoted their life to training for this one event.<br>
This fall, Atlanta will remain a busy place when Disaster Recovery Journal's 15th conference returns to that city. This event will be attended by hundreds of business continuity planners, like you, who are devoted to the profession.
And like Olympic athletes,  continuity planners are constantly striving to improve their skills and perfect their methods.<br>
That's why we've assembled the brightest and best the disaster recovery world has to offer to conduct sessions at this symposium. They'll provide timely tips, lessons learned and technological information to which every disaster recovery planner can relate. <br>
Our conference is arranged so that both the novice and experienced planners can gain valuable new information and learn how to apply it to their own personal situations.<br>
To join us in Atlanta, sign up for the sessions of your choice on the registration form on page 16 of this brochure. Additional information about  the conference's offerings can be found below.<br>





      









<br>
