<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> DRJ Expo </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<body background="stone.jpg">
<center>
<img src="line.gif"><br>
<img src="drjlogo.gif"><br>
<img src="line.gif"><br>
</center>

<center><font size="6">
THE
EIGHTH<br> 
INTERNATIONAL<br> 
DISASTER 
RECOVERY <br>
SYMPOSIUM 
AND
EXHIBITION<br></font size>
<br>
<font size="4">
September 9 - 11, 1996<br>
Atlanta, GA<br>
Disaster Recovery Journal presents its 15th conference<br></center></font size>
<br>
<br>
OVERVIEW<br>
<br>
Although the Olympics in Atlanta may be over by September, there's still a good reason to travel to this southern city.
Atlanta will be the site of Disaster Recovery Journal's 15th conference .  This conference promises to provide the best information available in the contingency planning field.<br>
Everything from the latest in technology to case studies of recovery from previous disasters will be covered in our sessions and workshops.<br>
The topics are presented so that everyone, from beginners to experienced contingency planners, will benefit by attending.<br>
<br>
<br>
GENERAL SESSIONS<br>
<br>
Our general sessions cover information which should be of interest to all our attendees. The speakers are well-known in the industry and knowledgable of trends and state-of-the-art technology.
Two General Sessions are held each morning. On Wednesday, an attendance prize drawing will be held immediately following the General Session 5. <br>
<br><br>
BREAKOUT SESSIONS<br>
<br>
Breakout sessions provide an opportunity for individuals to attend sessions covering topics of their own interests.  Attendees may select two of the ten sessions offered on Monday afternoon. 
The sessions are arranged by five subjects: Managerial; Technical; Communications; Emergency Response; and Strategic. <br>
<br>
ISSUES AND ANSWERS<br>
<br>
We'll again feature our popular "Issues and Answers" session at this conference. 
The session is an open forum allowing attendees to find answers to questions or problems they're having. It will be held on Wednesday morning.
Questions for the forum need to be submitted in advance. Please include your question or concern on the registration form on page 5.<br>
<br><br>
WORKSHOPS<br>
<br>
Six workshops are held on Tuesday afternoon;  attendees select the one of greatest interest to them.
These three-hour sessions feature an opportunity for attendees to cover a subject in an in-depth manner. Hands-on attention will be provided by the workshop speaker. These workshops are available at no additional cost.<br>
<br><br>
EXHIBITION<br>
<br>
Our conferences' exhibitions always feature more than 80 booths manned by exhibitors who are the industry leaders. These  companies display the latest products and services available in the contingency planning field.
The exhibits, open on Monday and Tuesday, are housed in the same building as the conference, making it convenient to view booths during breaks and lunch.<br>
<br>
CERTIFICATION COURSES<br>
<br>
DRI International will offer their certification and special courses following the close of the conference. Classes begin on Wednesday afternoon and continue through Friday. For more information, see pages 6 and 7.<br>
<br><br>
