September 9 - 11, 1996<br>
Atlanta, GA<br>
Disaster Recovery Journal presents its 15th conference<br></center></font size>
<br>
Remodeled
 Facility<br>
<br>
The Hyatt Regency Atlanta, located in the heart of downtown Atlanta,  has expanded its conference facilities to include  180,000 square feet of ballroom, exhibit, meeting and hospitality space, all under one roof. These accomodations provide  convenience and accessiblity for guests, making it  perfect for the business traveler. The hotel, located just 15 minutes from Hartsfield International Airport, has four restaurants, three lounges, an outdoor pool, spa and terrace.<br>
<br>
<br>
New Exhibit
Area<br>
<br>
The hotel's recently remodeled exhibit hall features  40,000-feet of display space as well as a variety of meeting rooms.  The exhibit area  is  located one  level below the Ballroom Level, where sessions will be held.<br>
<br>
<br>
Registration
Discounts<br>
<br>
Three or  more employees from the same company who register at the same time are eligible for a 10% discount. All contingency group members and CDRPs  are eligible for a 10% discount.  No refunds of the discount will be issued and the discount must be requested at the time of registration. Only one discount per registrant will apply.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Expanded
General 
Sessions<br>
<br>
General Sessions have been extended to allow more time for attendee participation. The longer sessions will feature more detailed information and allow more time for questions and answers.<br>
<br>
<br>
Exhibitor
Product Demos<br>
<br>
Exhibitor product demonstrations will be held on Monday and Tuesday. Exhibitors will host demonstrations in meeting rooms or in the exhibit area. A  list  of  exhibitors who will be participating will be available.<br>
<br>
<br>
Extended
Lunches<br>
<br>
Expanded lunches are available Monday and Tuesday to allow attendees to spend more time at the exhibit area. Lunches will be served from 11:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. and 12:30 p.m.-1:30 p.m. Wednesday lunch will be served from 11:30 a.m.-1:00 p.m. Industry Round Tables  will be available during both lunch periods.<br>
