<HEAD>
<TITLE>Exhibitors Welcome Letter </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<body background="stone.jpg">
Dear Exhibitor:<br>
<br>
Disaster Recovery Journal<br>
11337 ST. JOHN’S CHURCH ROAD<br>
     ST. LOUIS, MO 63123<br>
(314) 894-0276<br>
  FAX: (314) 894-7474<br>
INTERNET: www.drj.com<br>
<br>
<br>
Enclosed you’ll find the contract for exhibiting in Atlanta, GA, on September 8-10, 1996. Also 
enclosed are forms for "Exhibitor Badges" and  "Directory Information." The entire conference and
exhibition will be held in the Hyatt’s new meeting and event facility. The new Grand Hall features
40,000 sq. feet of space with wall to wall carpeting and 15 foot finished ceilings. (See attached
flyer)<br>
<br>
Please fill out the contract and fax or mail it back along with your booth payment. Booths will be
assigned on a "FIRST PAID, FIRST SERVED" basis.<br>
<br>
If you have prepaid for your booth, you need to fill out the contract, select a booth preference, and
fax it back to me as soon as possible. If you have not Prepaid for a booth, fill out the contract and
fax it back to me; drop the original in the mail, along with your check; and I will assign you a booth
once I receive payment.<br>
<br>
The "Exhibitor Badges" and "Directory Information" forms are due back by August 2, 1996. If we
do not receive these forms on time, you will not be included in the Exhibitor Directory, and will not
have proper badges for all your booth personnel.<br>
<br>
As always, we will have a Sunday evening Welcome Reception, and Exhibitor Product Demos
during Tuesday’s lunch and later Tuesday evening.<br>
<br>
We are looking forward to another successful conference, and we are doing everything possible to
make the exhibition successful for you. If you have any questions, please call. Additional detailed
information on product demos and the welcome reception will be mailed at a later date. I look
forward to seeing you in Atlanta!<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>

Bob Amold<br>
Exhibition Coordinator<br>

