<html>

<head>
<title>Weyerhaeuser Recovery Executive Summary</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="wood.gif">
<p><img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11> <img src="oscar.gif" align=left hspace=0 width=114 height=118> 
<img src="oscar.gif" align=right hspace=0 width=114 height=118> </p>
<hr>
<h2 align=center>Weyerhaeuser <br>
<font size=7><i>R</i></font><i>ecovery </i><font size=7><i>E</i></font><i>xecutive </i><font size=7><i>S</i></font><i>ummary </i></h2>
<hr>
<p><br clear=left>
<img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11><br>
<br>
</p>
<h4>Organizations considering our service are seeking a qualified, highly experienced company to provide a solution to 
their disaster recovery requirements. We believe this should include a program consisting of facilities designed 
and used exclusively for recovery, skilled contingency planning resources, trained technical and operational 
support, supported by a comprehensive plan for testing/rehearsals that confirms the ability to satisfactorily 
recover from any disaster. When implemented, this comprehensive program will assure a successful recovery 
during any unanticipated interruption.</h4>
<h4>Weyerhaeuser Recovery Services proposes its program based on a unique recovery philosophy. This philosophy 
encompasses four major thrusts:</h4>
<ul>
<li>To quickly reach a point that, together, we will have developed, documented and proven our ability to recover the 
critical business functions in addition to data center support.</li>
<li>A dual focus that deals with the personal impact of any unanticipated interruption on the staff, along with the critical 
technology so, that we get <i>people </i>back to work as well as the computer systems.</li>
<li>Fully functional <i>remote </i>as well as <i>on-site </i>rehearsals, so that all recovery options (which will have been fully rehearsed 
and well documented) can be considered. The appropriate one can be chosen to reflect the nature of the event.</li>
<li>A well documented contingency plan, supported by a full range of rehearsal techniques; designed to simulate a broad 
spectrum of events so that each and every impacted employee understands the importance of their role in a successful 
recovery.</li>
</ul>
<h4>In conclusion, it is our commitment to plan, rehearse, and document in a manner that will assure successful 
recovery regardless of the length or type of outage suffered.</h4>
<p><br>
<img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11><br>
<br>
</p>
<h3><img src="vlogo.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=15><a href="links2.html">Return to Weyerhaeuser's Contents and Links</a></h3>
