http://www.drj.com:80/Weyerhaeuser/philo.html 205.139.224.137 19970124115318 text/html 4038
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Date: Fri, 24 Jan 1997 12:09:26 GMT
Server: Apache/1.1.1
Content-type: text/html
Set-Cookie: Apache=widener22395854107766812; path=/
</DOCHDR>
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">

<html>

<head>
<title>Weyerhaeuser Disaster Recovery Services Philosophy</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="wood.gif">
<p><img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11> <img src="oscar.gif" align=left hspace=0 width=114 height=118> 
<img src="oscar.gif" align=right hspace=0 width=114 height=118> </p>
<hr>
<h2 align=center>Weyerhaeuser <br>
<font size=7><i>D</i></font><i>isaster </i><font size=7><i>R</i></font><i>ecovery </i><font size=7><i>P</i></font><i>hilosophy</i> </h2>
<hr>
<p><br clear=left>
<img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11><br>
</p>
<h4>Our systems are housed in our comprehensive hot-site facilities which are dedicated to disaster recovery. These 
sites are located in Federal Way, Washington (near Seattle) and Valley Forge, Pennsylvania (near Philadelphia). 
Beyond meeting our subscribers technology requirements, we call your attention to several key business elements 
of our plan/philosophy.</h4>
<ul>
<li>Uniquely, we limit the number of participants we allow into our program, thereby assuring access to the hotsite for either 
recovery or rehearsals. This industry low contract to capability ratio policy assures our subscribers that the equipment is 
available for testing and that our subscriber's plan and personnel are well known to us. In the event of a disaster (or 
rehearsals), this close relationship means that we will be well into the recovery process before our subscriber's 
personnel even arrive.</li>
<li>Our rehearsal methods focus on business resumption and include on-site technical rehearsals, remote rehearsals and 
employee awareness reviews. We anticipate the entire spectrum of possible occurrences; from relatively short-term 
outages to major catastrophes. There is no additional cost for any of the several strategic and/or tactical rehearsals that 
we support. We encourage them, and look forward to participating in them.</li>
<li>A significant resource included in every agreement is our staff of highly skilled and experienced contingency planners. A 
recovery plan needs to be dynamic. Our planners are prepared to assist our subscribers with plan development and 
reviews reflecting each subscriber's changing environment.</li>
<li>Our planning and rehearsal techniques are designed to anticipate and support a wide variety of unscheduled 
interruptions; from those of a catastrophic nature, which would require relocation to the hot-site for a protracted period, 
to those more frequently experienced occurrences which tend to be localized to a given area, such as the data center. 
Where it is possible to recover without relocation to a hot-site, our program anticipates establishing a remote site at or 
near our subscriber's current facility.</li>
<li>Should our subscribers either need or desire to relocate to the hot-site, our service is all-inclusive. People can arrive 
without any payment capacity, our program takes their well-being into account as a fundamental part of successful 
recovery. They can eat in our dining facilities, exercise in our health clubs, all without having to concern themselves with 
payment. They are then prepared and ready to focus on getting the business back in business. They are supported by 
auxilliary services, such as our bulk mail facility, secretarial and dictation facilities, conference and meeting rooms, and 
copy and fax machines. In short, beyond getting our subscriber's systems operational, we help them get their business 
back in business!</li>
</ul>
<p><img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11><br>
</p>
