<html>

<head>
<title>Weyerhaeuser Disaster Recovery Facilities - Federal Way, WA</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="wood.gif">
<p><img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11> <img src="sea13.gif" align=left hspace=0 width=128 height=79> 
<img src="sea21.gif" align=right hspace=0 width=129 height=80></p>
<hr>
<h2 align=center>Weyerhaeuser <br>
<font size=7><i>R</i></font><i>ecovery </i><font size=7><i>F</i></font><i>acilities</i></h2>
<hr width=75%>
<p><img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11><br>
</p>
<h3>Federal Way, Washington</h3>
<h3>Facility Description:</h3>
<h4><b>Dedicated</b> hot-site is self-contained within Weyerhaeuser's <b>450,000</b> square foot Technology Center, which is 
owned by Weyerhaeuser, operated by Weyerhaeuser personnel, and on Weyerhaeuser property.</h4>
<p><br>
</p>
<h4>Work areas with telephones and terminals for both technical and operational people are dedicated exclusively to 
you while on site.</h4>
<h4>High-speed duplicating, word processing, microfilm, and microfiche facilities on site.</h4>
<h4>Meeting rooms, office space, operation ready rooms, and a restaurant-style cafeteria are all included and on site.</h4>
<p><br>
</p>
<h4>A complete exercise facility including handball, and raquetball courts, universal and free weights, indoor tennis 
(pickleball), treadmills, stationary bikes, and rowing machines, fully equipped locker and shower rooms.</h4>
<p><img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11><br>
<br>
</p>
<h3>Facility Features:</h3>
<h4>The Recovery Center has 120 tons of air.</h4>
<h4>The Recovery Center 60 HZ and 400 cycle-conditioned power. Power is conditioned through MG set.</h4>
<h4>The Recovery Center is certified to be free of all magnetic fields.</h4>
<h4>All power distribution systems are on UPS and commercial power is backed up with our diesel generator. We have 
a fuel supply assuring the entire recovery facility with power for over a month of continuous operation.</h4>
<h4>The Center is served by three geographically separated telephone central offices.</h4>
<h4>The control center is staffed 7 days a week, 24 hours a day</h4>
<h4>Disaster Recovery personnel are on pagers 7 days a week, 24 hours a day.</h4>
<h4>All employees, visitors and subscribers are required to use and meet security regulations and standards.</h4>
<h4>TV Monitors are used 7 days a week, 24 hours a day with magnetic card access employed on all Recovery Center 
doors. Video surveillance is used on all external doors in hallways with on-foot security patrols at least each hour.</h4>
<h4>Safety checks are made on all systems at least every 3 months with all logs and forms available for review.</h4>
<h4>Fire protection is provided by Halon under the floor and water above dry-charged to the external walls; smoke 
detectors, heat rate of rise and water detectors are employed; all doors and walls are fire rated at 2+ hours; fire 
drills are conducted at minimum every 6 months with fire inspections made every 3 months.</h4>
<h4>Temperature and humidity is monitored 7 days a week, 24 hours a day.</h4>
<p><br>
<img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11><br>
</p>
<h3>Facility Logistics</h3>
<h4>Weyerhaeuser's disaster recovery facility is conveniently located close to SeaTac International Airport which is 
served by all major airlines.</h4>
<h4>Travel arrangements can be handled for our subscribers by our travel service.</h4>
<h4>Transportation can be provided by Weyerhaeuser's corporate-owned jet aircraft fleet.</h4>
<h4>If our subscriber chooses to arrive in their own corporate jet, use of our hangar and parking is provided at Sea-Tac 
International Airport.</h4>
<h4>Rental cars are available from Hertz, Budget, National, and others, and are conveniently located to the recovery 
center.</h4>
<h4>A restaurant is available within the Technology Center with many others close by that span the range of culinary 
interest from fast food to gourmet.</h4>
<p><img src="line_mar.gif" align=bottom width=750 height=11><br>
<br>
</p>
