<h4>The Recovery Center has 120 tons of air.</h4>
<h4>The Recovery Center 60 HZ and 400 cycle-conditioned power. Power is conditioned through MG set.</h4>
<h4>The Recovery Center is certified to be free of all magnetic fields.</h4>
<h4>All power distribution systems are on UPS and commercial power is backed up with our diesel generator. We have 
a fuel supply assuring the entire recovery facility with power for over a month of continuous operation.</h4>
<h4>The center is served by multiple telephone central offices and a fiber loop operated by a local exchange.</h4>
<h4>The control center is staffed 7 days a week, 24 hours a day.</h4>
<h4>Disaster Recovery personnel are on pagers 7 days a week, 24 hours a day.</h4>
<h4>All employees, visitors and subscribers are required to use and meet security regulations and standards.</h4>
<h4>TV Monitors are used 7 days a week, 24 hours a day with magnetic card access employed on all Recovery Center 
doors. Video surveillance is used on all external doors in hallways with on-foot security patrols at least each hour.</h4>
<h4>Safety checks are made on all systems at least every 3 months with all logs and forms available for review.</h4>
<h4>Fire protection is provided by Halon under the floor and water above; smoke detectors; heat rate of rise and water 
detectors are employed; doors and walls are fire rated; fire drills are conducted at minimum every 6 months with 
fire inspections made every 3 months</h4>
