<p><h2>A survey of international banking</h2><P>April 27th, 1996<HR><b>Bibliography</b></p><p>"The Decline of Traditional Banking: Implications for Financial Stability and Regulatory Policy", by Franklin Edwards and Frederic Mishkin. <i>Economic Policy Review</i>, Federal Reserve Bank of New York, July 1995.<p>"Market Discipline as a Regulator of Bank Risk", by Arthur Rolnick. In "Safeguarding the Banking System in an Environment of Financial Cycles". Federal Reserve Bank of Boston, 1993.<p>"The Central Bank and the Financial System", by C.A.E. Goodhart. MacMillan, 1995.<p>"The Global Financial System". Harvard University Press, 1995.<p>"Systemic Stability and Competitive Neutrality Issues", by Harald Benink and David Llewellyn. <i>Journal of Financial Services Research</i>, Vol 9, No 3/4, December 1995.<p>"Financial Regulation in the Global Economy", by Richard Herring and Robert Litan. <p>The Brookings Institution; "Some Regulatory Concerns", by Charles Goodhart. LSE.<p>"International Financial Markets and Systemic Risk", by Morris Goldstein. <p>Institute for International Economics; "Narrow Banking Reconsidered", by Ronnie Phillips. <p>Jerome Levy Economics Institute; "Sustaining Safety and Soundness" , by Allan Meltzer. The World Bank. <p><HR><br><p align=center><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?830559600,sur">Search</a>
